      "text": "For the past year I come across conversations about the need to fix current state of academic research, mainly publishing. What supposed to be open is, in reality closed. Academics are paranoid about sharing results of their research before publishing, because they are worried about being published and their [[Citation Index]] Their sustainability model comes from further research grants or collaboration with the industry. All of the above makes it difficult for academia to be cutting edge."
